12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 10 O.S. 2021, Section 601.1, as
14 amended by Section 2, Chapter 347, O.S.L. 2024 (10 O.S. Supp. 2025,
15 Section 601.1), is amended to read as follows:
16 Section 601.1. A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma
17 Commission on Children and Youth which shall be composed of eighteen
18 (18) seventeen (17) members. The membership shall include:
19 1. The Director of the Department of Human Services, the State
20 Commissioner of Health, the Commissioner of the Department of Mental
21 Health and Substance Abuse Services, the State Superintendent of
22 Public Instruction, the Administrator of the Oklahoma Health Care
23 Authority, the Director of the State Department of Rehabilitation
24 Services, and the Chair of the SJR 13 Oversight Committee;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1572 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 2. The Executive Director of the Office of Juvenile Affairs;
2 3. Five members who shall be appointed by the Governor from a
3 list submitted by the governing board of each of the following
4 organizations:
5 a. the Oklahoma Children’s Agencies and Residential
6 Enterprises,
7 b. one statewide association of youth services,
8 c. the Oklahoma Bar Association,
9 d. the Oklahoma District Attorneys Association, and
10 e. a statewide court-appointed Special Advocate
11 Association;
12 4. 3. One member appointed by the Governor who shall represent
13 one of the metropolitan juvenile bureaus;
14 5. 4. One member representing business or industry, appointed
15 by the Governor;
16 6. 5. One member who is the parent of a child with special
17 needs, appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives;
18 7. 6. One member with a demonstrated interest in improving
19 children’s services who is not employed by a state agency or a
20 private organization that receives state funds, appointed by the
21 President Pro Tempore of the Senate; and
22 8. 7. One member who shall be appointed by the Governor from a
23 list of three names submitted by the Post Adjudication Review Board.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1572 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 B. The appointed members shall have had active experience in
2 services to children and youth and may serve four (4) terms of two
3 (2) years each. A person appointed to fill the remainder of a
4 vacant term shall, upon completion of that term, be eligible to
5 serve four (4) additional two-year terms. Terms shall coincide with
6 the fiscal year.
7 C. The Oklahoma Commission on Children and Youth shall provide
8 a report on Commission member attendance to the appointing
9 authorities following each Commission meeting.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
11 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
15 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
